# Roadmap Item Fields

Optional fields items in `roadmap.yaml` may carry:

- `links:` ‚Äî array of paths (relative to repo root) to plans/specs for this item.
- `notes:` ‚Äî markdown string with timestamped context notes.
- `doc_update:` ‚Äî ISO date (`2026-04-28`) or `skipped ‚Äî <reason>`; required for `done` items of type feature/bug/refactor. The validator warns when absent.
- `spawned_from:` ‚Äî id of the item that surfaced this one.
- `superseded_by:` ‚Äî id of the item that replaced this one. Item must be `dropped`.
- `related:` ‚Äî peer item ids (not parent‚Äìchild).
- `phases:` ‚Äî `[{ id, title, status, completed_at?, notes? }]` for multi-phase items. Item-level `status` is derived when `phases:` is present.
- `affects:` ‚Äî `[layer-id]` (same scope) or `[scope-id:layer-id]` (cross-scope).
- `done_when:` ‚Äî 1‚Äì3 plain-English bullets defining done.
- `files_to_read:` ‚Äî repo-relative paths an implementer should read first.
- `risks:` ‚Äî known unknowns or complicating factors.
- `priority:` ‚Äî `p0` (critical) / `p1` (high) / `p2` (normal) / `p3` (low). Advisory only ‚Äî does not affect ordering.
- `type:` ‚Äî `feature` / `bug` / `refactor` / `spike`.
- `goal_ref:` ‚Äî array of goal IDs from `overview.md` (`[g1]`, `[g2, g3]`) OR the literal string `exploratory`. Default cardinality is **single primary** ‚Äî one entry the rationale is anchored to. Use a multi-entry list only for genuinely cross-cutting items. Children may diverge from their parent's `goal_ref` if they advance a different goal ‚Äî surface the divergence to the user at plan time. `exploratory` is the deliberate escape hatch for items captured without a clear goal connection; they're excluded from default Recommend output but visible in the dashboard. Missing entirely ‚Üí validator warning (not error) ‚Äî backwards-compatible.
- `workpad:` ‚Äî repo-relative path to a workpad file (e.g., `.tenbo/workpads/ed-045.md`). Created for substantial items at plan-path triage. See `workpad-protocol.md`.
- `dispatch_attempts:` ‚Äî integer, incremented when an item enters `rework` after a prior attempt failed. Validator surfaces items with `dispatch_attempts >= 3` to flag chronic difficulty. Items with status `rework` are mid-reset; the workpad has been archived and a fresh one created. See SKILL.md "Rework path".
- `bar_override:` ‚Äî string reason set when the user explicitly bypasses the completion bar. Validator surfaces overridden items in health checks. See `completion-bar.md`.

**Spec files:** When creating a plan or spec, include `tenbo_item: <id>` in the file's frontmatter and append its path to the item's `links:`.

**Notes:** When the user adds context ("note on X: ‚Ä¶"), append a timestamped bullet to `notes:`.

**Workpad vs. notes:** `notes:` is for short context bullets the user dictates inline. `workpad:` is the structured living document Tenbo authors for substantial in-flight work. Lightweight items use `notes:` only; substantial items use both, with workpad as the durable execution state.
